@startuml Data Pipeline - Hotel Management Server

!define ICONURL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tupadr3/plantuml-icon-font-sprites/v3.0.0/icons
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Inter
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #555555
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam PartitionBackgroundColor #F0F4FF
skinparam PartitionBorderColor #8888CC

title **Hotel Management Server — Data Pipeline Diagram**\n End-to-end data flow across all major operations

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════
'  1. AUTHENTICATION & TOKEN PIPELINE
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════

start

partition "**Authentication Pipeline**" #AliceBlue {
  :Client sends **POST /api/v1/auth/login**
with { email, password };

: **Throttler** (10 req/60s) >>
: **ValidationPipe** (whitelist DTO) >>
: **\@Public()** bypasses JwtAuthGuard;

: **AuthService.login()**;

:Fetch user by email from
**v_users** (MySQL View);

: **HashService.comparePassword()**
Compare bcrypt hash;

if (Password correct?) then (yes)
  :Generate **Access Token** (2h)
  + **Refresh Token** (7d)
  via **JwtService.signAsync()**;

  :Store Refresh Token in **tokens** table
  via **sp_update_refresh_token()**
  (linked to user + user-agent);

  :Return { accessToken, refreshToken };
else (no)
  :Throw **UnauthorizedException**;
  stop
endif

' ── Subsequent Authenticated Requests ──
:Client sends request with
**Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>**;

: **JwtAuthGuard** extracts token >>
: **AccessTokenStrategy.validate()**
Check if token is in **blacklistedTokens**
(in-memory Map + DB);

if (Token valid & not blacklisted?) then (yes)
  :Attach user payload { sub, email, role }
  to **request.user**;

  : **RolesGuard** checks \@Roles() decorator;

  if (User has required role?) then (yes)
    :Proceed to Controller;
  else (no)
    :Throw **ForbiddenException**;
    stop
  endif
else (no)
  :Throw **UnauthorizedException**;
  stop
endif

' ── Logout Pipeline ──
:Client sends **POST /api/v1/auth/logout**;

:Remove refresh token from **tokens** table
via **sp_remove_token(userId, agent)**;

:Add access token to **blacklistedTokens**
(in-memory Map + **blacklisted_tokens** DB table)
with expiry timestamp;

:Hourly cleanup of expired blacklisted tokens
(setInterval → Map.delete + DB DELETE);

}

partition "**Booking Lifecycle Pipeline**" #Honeydew {

' ── Step 1: Check Availability ──
partition "**Phase 1: Availability Check**" {
  :Customer/Staff queries
  **GET /api/v1/bookings/available**
  ?roomTypeId, checkIn, checkOut, capacity;

  :Call **sp_find_available_room_types()**
  to find rooms not conflicting
  with existing bookings;

  :Return list of available room types
  with pricing + capacity info;
}

' ── Step 2: Create Booking ──
partition "**Phase 2: Create Booking**" {
  :Client sends **POST /api/v1/bookings**
  { customerId, staffId, checkInDate,
    checkOutDate, roomTypeId,
    roomIds[], services[]?, discount? };

  :Generate **UUID** (full) + **shortId** (last 6 chars);

  :Call **sp_create_booking()** with:
  id, shortId, customerId, staffId,
  checkInDate, checkOutDate, roomTypeId,
  JSON(roomIds), JSON(services), discount;

  note right
    The Stored Procedure handles:
    • INSERT into **bookings**
    • INSERT into **booking_rooms** (each roomId)
    • INSERT into **booking_services** (if any)
    • Calculate **total_room_price**
    • Status = '**Pending**'
  end note

  :Fetch created booking via
  **sp_find_booking_by_id()**
  (returns: booking + rooms + services);

  fork
    :Fetch customer email from **users** table;
    : **MailService.sendBookingCreatedMail()**
    → SMTP → Customer inbox;
  fork again
    :Return { id } to client;
  end fork
}

' ── Step 3: Confirm Booking ──
partition "**Phase 3: Confirm Booking**" {
  :Staff sends **PATCH /api/v1/bookings/confirm/:id**;

  :BEGIN TRANSACTION;

  :SELECT * FROM bookings WHERE id = ? **FOR UPDATE**
  (Row-level lock prevents concurrent confirm);

  if (Status == 'Pending'?) then (yes)
    :UPDATE bookings SET status = '**Confirmed**';
    :COMMIT;

    fork
      : **MailService.sendBookingConfirmedMail()**;
    fork again
      :Return confirmed booking details;
    end fork
  else (no)
    :ROLLBACK;
    :Throw **BadRequestException**;
    stop
  endif
}

' ── Step 4: Check-In ──
partition "**Phase 4: Check-In**" {
  :Staff sends **PATCH /api/v1/bookings/check-in/:id**;

  :Pre-check via **v_bookings** (no lock, fast-fail);

  if (Status == 'Confirmed'?) then (yes)
    :BEGIN TRANSACTION
    (**DatabaseService.withTransaction()**);

    :Lock: SELECT ... FOR UPDATE;
    :Re-validate status after lock
    (prevents race condition);

    :UPDATE via **sp_update_booking()**
    status → '**Checked-in**'
    actual_check_in → NOW();

    :COMMIT;
    :Return { id };
  else (no)
    :Throw **BadRequestException**;
    stop
  endif
}

' ── Step 4.5: Add Services During Stay ──
partition "**Phase 4.5: Add Services to Booking**" {
  :Staff sends **POST /api/v1/services/booking/:bookingId**
  { service_id, quantity };

  :Pre-check: booking not Checked-out/Cancelled;

  :Sort [bookingId, serviceId] alphabetically
  for **consistent lock ordering** (deadlock prevention);

  :BEGIN TRANSACTION;

  :Lock both booking + service rows **in sorted order**;

  :Read service price/quantity after lock
  (ensures latest data);

  if (Service active & sufficient stock?) then (yes)
    :INSERT into **booking_services**
    (id, booking_id, service_id, quantity, price, used_at);

    if (Service has finite stock?) then (yes)
      :UPDATE services SET quantity = quantity - N
      Auto-deactivate if stock depleted;
    endif

    :UPDATE bookings SET
    total_service_price = SUM(bs.price * bs.quantity)
    grand_total = total_room_price + total_service_price;

    :COMMIT;
    :Return { id };
  else (no)
    :ROLLBACK;
    :Throw **BadRequestException**;
    stop
  endif
}

' ── Step 5: Check-Out ──
partition "**Phase 5: Check-Out**" {
  :Staff sends **PATCH /api/v1/bookings/check-out/:id**;

  :Pre-check via v_bookings (fast-fail);

  if (Status == 'Checked-in'?) then (yes)
    :BEGIN TRANSACTION
    Isolation: **REPEATABLE READ**
    (**withTransactionIsolation()**);

    :Lock: SELECT ... FOR UPDATE
    (blocks addToBooking from adding
    services during checkout);

    :Calculate final pricing AFTER lock:
    total_room_price + SUM(service*qty)
    = grand_total;

    :UPDATE via **sp_update_booking()**
    status → '**Checked-out**'
    actual_check_out → NOW()
    total_room_price, total_service_price,
    grand_total;

    :COMMIT;
    :Return { id };
  else (no)
    :Throw **BadRequestException**;
    stop
  endif
}

}

partition "**Payment & Invoice Pipeline**" #LemonChiffon {

partition "**Phase A: QR Code Generation**" {
  :Client requests **GET /api/v1/bookings/qr**
  ?amount=X&description=Y;

  :Build VietQR URL:
  https://img.vietqr.io/image/
  {bankId}-{accountNo}-{template}.png
  ?amount=X&addInfo=Y&accountName=Z;

  :Return QR URL to client for display;
}

partition "**Phase B: SePay Webhook Processing**" {
  :SePay sends **POST /api/v1/webhook/sepay**
  { id, content, transferAmount, ... }
  with **Authorization: Bearer <API_KEY>**;

  :\@Public() - no JWT required;
  :Validate API Key from header;

  :BEGIN TRANSACTION;

  :Idempotency check: SELECT from **payments**
  WHERE transaction_id = payload.id;

  if (Already processed?) then (yes)
    :ROLLBACK;
    :Return silently (idempotent);
    stop
  endif

  :Extract **shortId** from payload.content
  (last 6 chars, uppercase);

  :SELECT * FROM bookings WHERE
  short_id = ? **FOR UPDATE**;

  if (Booking found?) then (yes)
    :INSERT INTO **payments**
    (id, booking_id, amount,
    payment_method='Bank Transfer',
    payment_status='Completed',
    transaction_id);

    :UPDATE bookings SET
    deposit = deposit + transferAmount;

    :COMMIT;

    :Read updated booking from **v_bookings**;

    if (deposit + discount >= grandTotal?) then (fully paid)
      : **WebhookService.createInvoice()**;
      :Generate unique **invoice_number**;
      :INSERT INTO **invoices**
      (id, booking_id, invoice_number,
      total_amount, issued_date);
    endif

    fork
      : **MailService.sendPaymentReceivedMail()**
      Include: amount paid, total paid,
      grand total, fully paid status;
    fork again
      :Return updated booking;
    end fork
  else (no)
    :ROLLBACK;
    :Log warning: booking not found;
    stop
  endif
}

|#MistyRose|  Scheduled Tasks Pipeline  |

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════
'  4. CRON JOBS / SCHEDULED TASKS
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════

partition "**Cron: Every Day at 9 AM**" {

  fork
    ' ── Auto-Cancel Stale Pending Bookings ──
    : **BookingsScheduler.handlePendingBookings()**;

    :Query all bookings with status = '**Pending**'
    JOIN users for contact info;

    while (For each pending booking) is (next)
      :Calculate age = NOW() - created_at;

      if (Age > 3 days?) then (yes)
        :UPDATE bookings SET
        status = '**Cancelled**';

        : **MailService.sendBookingCancelledMail()**
        → Email: auto-cancelled notification;
      else (no)
        : **MailService.sendPendingReminderMail()**
        → Email: please confirm your booking;
      endif
    endwhile (done)

  fork again
    ' ── Check-In Reminders for Confirmed Bookings ──
    : **BookingsScheduler.handleCheckingReminders()**;

    :Query all bookings with status = '**Confirmed**'
    JOIN users for contact info;

    while (For each confirmed booking) is (next)
      :Calculate daysUntilCheckIn =
      checkInDate - today;

      if (1 day before?) then (yes)
        : **MailService.sendBookingReminderMail()**
        isFinal = true
        → "Check-in tomorrow!";
      elseif (Every 7 days before?) then (yes)
        : **MailService.sendBookingReminderMail()**
        isFinal = false
        → "Your stay is approaching";
      endif
    endwhile (done)
  end fork
}

|#Lavender|  File Upload Pipeline  |

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════
'  5. FILE UPLOAD PIPELINE
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════

partition "**Image Upload Flow**" {
  :Admin sends **POST /api/v1/upload/images**
  or **POST /api/v1/upload/room-type-images**
  multipart/form-data (max 10 files, 5MB each);

  : **FilesInterceptor** validates:
  • File extension: jpg, jpeg, png only
  • File size: max 5MB per file;

  :For each file:
  Generate **UUID** filename
  → S3 key: images/{uuid}.{ext};

  : **S3Client.send(PutObjectCommand)**
  Upload to **AWS S3** bucket
  (ap-southeast-1);

  :Construct public URL:
  https://{bucket}.s3.{region}.amazonaws.com/
  images/{uuid}.{ext};

  if (room-type-images endpoint?) then (yes)
    :Fetch existing room type images
    via **RoomTypesService.findOne()**;

    :Merge: existingImages + newUrls;

    :Update room type via
    **sp_update_room_type()**
    with JSON(mergedImages);
  endif

  :Return { urls[] };
}

|#FFEEEE|  Reporting & Analytics Pipeline  |

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════
'  6. REPORTING & ANALYTICS PIPELINE
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════

partition "**Dashboard Summary**" {
  :Admin/Staff requests **GET /api/v1/reports/summary**
  ?startDate, endDate, type=[day|month|year];

  fork
    : **getRoomStats()**
    Aggregate from **bookings** + **booking_rooms**
    + **rooms** + **room_types**;

    :Output: totalBookings, cancelled,
    completed, active, byRoomType[];
  fork again
    : **getRevenueStats()**
    Aggregate from **bookings**
    (exclude Cancelled + Pending);

    :Group by period (DATE / MONTH / YEAR);

    :Output: timeline[], summary
    { totalRevenue, roomRevenue,
    serviceRevenue, totalInvoices };
  fork again
    : **getCustomerStats()**
    Aggregate from **bookings** + **users** + **roles**;

    :Output: activeCustomers, newCustomers,
    topCustomers[] (top 10 by spend);
  end fork

  :Combine all stats into unified
  summary response;
}

partition "**CSV Export**" {
  :Admin/Staff requests **GET /api/v1/reports/export**;

  :Reuse **getRevenueStats()** query;

  :Build CSV string:
  Period, Total Revenue, Room Revenue,
  Service Revenue, Discount;

  :Set response headers:
  Content-Type: text/csv
  Content-Disposition: attachment;

  :Stream CSV to client;
}

|#F0F0FF|  System Logging Pipeline  |

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════
'  7. SYSTEM LOGGING PIPELINE
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════

:Every HTTP request enters
**LoggingInterceptor** (Global);

fork
  :On **SUCCESS**:
  Log: userId, method+url,
  IP, userAgent,
  "SUCCESS - status: {code}";
fork again
  :On **ERROR**:
  Log: userId, method+url,
  IP, userAgent,
  "ERROR - {error.message}";
end fork

:INSERT INTO **system_logs** via
**SystemLogsService.create()**
{ id(uuid), userId, action,
ip, userAgent, description };

:Admin/Staff queries logs via
**GET /api/v1/system-logs**
?page, limit, userId, action;

:Return paginated audit trail;

stop

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════
'  LEGEND
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════
legend right
  |= Symbol |= Meaning |
  | **: ** | Data transformation / processing step |
  | **FOR UPDATE** | Row-level pessimistic lock (MySQL) |
  | **sp_** | Stored Procedure call |
  | **v_** | Database View |
  | **fork** | Parallel / async execution |
  | **Cron** | \@nestjs/schedule timed job |
endlegend

@enduml
